definition.text:
unta'kn.
1. Not taken; not seized; not apprehended; as a thief untaken
2. Not reduced; not subdued; as untaken Troy.
3. Not swallowed.UNTAKEN away, not removed. 2 Corinthians 3:1 4.UNTAKEN up, not occupied; not filled.Untalked of, not talked of; not made the subject of conversation.
